premise_source_doc_sentence: Garry Kimovich Kasparov  (  Га́рри Ки́мович Каспа́ров , -LSB- ˈɡarʲɪ ˈkʲiməvʲɪtɕ kɐˈsparəf -RSB- ; born Garik Kimovich Weinstein , 13 April 1963  )  is a Russian chess grandmaster , former World Chess Champion , writer , and political activist , whom many consider to be the greatest chess player of all time .

Starting from Volume 113  (  2012  )  , Chess Informant has introduced major changes in its structure , including several authors ' columns written in English , e.g. `` Garry 's choice '' by Garry Kasparov , `` Top Five '' by selected top grandmasters , `` Labs - theoretical surveys '' by ten selected grandmasters , etc. .

The Museum of Jewish Heritage is developing a special gallery relating to Jews in sports and chess , which will recognize `` major Jewish chess players such as Garry Kasparov , Mikhail Tal , and Judith Polgar '' .
